  "result": "**Root cause**: Two combined bugs blocked literals.lua at line 231 (`assert(sd == s1 and getadd(sd) ~= a1)`):\n\n1. `string.format(\"%p\", v)` in `crates/lua-stdlib/src/string_lib.rs:1691` returned the literal placeholder `\"(ptr)\"` for every value, so `getadd(sd) ~= a1` was always `\"(ptr)\" ~= \"(ptr)\"` → false.\n2. `intern_or_create_str` in `crates/lua-vm/src/state.rs:1391` interned strings of every length, so the runtime concat `\"0123…\" .. \"01234…\"` reused the same `LuaString` `Rc` as the same-content literal `s1` instead of producing a fresh long string (Lua 5.4's `luaS_newlstr` semantics: short interned, long always fresh).\n\n**Fix**:\n1. `%p` now formats `lua_vm::api::to_pointer(state, arg)` as `0x{:x}` — giving each `GcRef`'s identity-address a unique hex rendering.\n2. `intern_or_create_str` now mirrors `luaS_newlstr`: `len ≤ 40` interns globally, `> 40` allocates a fresh `LuaString` via `GcRef::new(LuaString::from_bytes(...))`, bypassing `interned_lt`.\n\n**New state**: The literals test now executes through ~5 `+` checkpoints (lines 143, 157, 163, 172, 203) before panicking on the deliberate `coroutine.resume` stub at `crates/lua-stdlib/src/coro_lib.rs:129` — i.e., the explicit Phase-A–D coroutine stub per PORTING.md §2 #6, which is outside the scope of this bug. The original `:18: \"\"` failure is gone.\n\nAll temporary `eprintln` instrumentation was removed; `cargo build -p lua-cli` is green (warnings only, no errors).",
